<HEADER>
A1829 &Cx1f; tad-z
r k BC-COMMENTARY-BJT27-COX     09-26 0546
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COMMENTARY-BJT27-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    COX NEWS SERVICE COMMENTARY BUDGET
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   These columns for release Wednesday, September 27, 2000 are
moving today to clients of the New York Times News Service.
</P>
<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ Howard Kleinberg says we don't need the
government to regulate the violence and sex in Hollywood's movies.
He says what's needed is a good dose of self-restraint from the
American public. (Kleinberg, Cox News Service). MOVED MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ This morning, as usual, coffee and conversation
with my retired farmer buddies began on a lofty note. Well, maybe
not quite so exalted, since we were talking politics. Amos was
saying how he wishes Lieberman would stop Bible thumping, and Cal
admits he keeps hoping for a miracle where Bush will stop talking
all over himself and say something _ almost anything. (Schuett, Cox
News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   JOEMURRAY _ Column from Dreamsville: Folks in a rural community
in the middle of Oklahoma in the 1930s figured they knew who the
chicken thieves were. They just couldn't catch them. Then the
sheriff came up with a plan to nab 'em in the act in the hen house.
Problem was, he got outfoxed. (Joe Murray, Cox News Service). MOVED
MONDAY.
</P>
<P>
   YOUNG-COLUMN _ So, Gandhi arrives at the portal of the
afterlife. A specter with a clipboard stops him. ``Why the delay?''
asks Gandhi. ``Have I not lived a moral life? Have I not fought
oppression and sacrificed for mankind?'' ``Yes, sir,'' says the
attendant. ``It says here, however, you haven't taken the algebra
exit test.'' You are entering testing purgatory. (Young, Waco
Tribune-Herald)
</P>
<P>
   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION FOR SUBSCRIBERS OF THE NYT NEWS
SERVICE
</P>
<P>
   Spot news budgets move daily at 2 p.m. and 6 p.m. Eastern.
Additionally, separate features and commentary budgets move at 10
a.m., and sports and business budgets at 6 p.m. Additional updates
are possible if news developments warrant.
</P>
<P>
   All times are Eastern unless otherwise noted. If stories will
move after 8 p.m., an ETA will be given.
</P>
