   LIFESTYLE
</P>
<P>
   E-LIVING _ A daily column featuring the most useful Web sites
and live online events affecting arts, entertainment and leisure
activites. Today: (Footlick, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TRAVEL-GETAWAY _The complete Southeast Tourism Society listing
of ``Top 20'' events for the months of October, November and
December. The 60 events, in the judgment of this nonprofit,
Atlanta-based travel promotions group, include well-known events
like the Natchez Fall Pilgrimage to more obscure fun like the Trigg
County Ham Festival in Cadiz, Ky. And, of course, lots and lots of
Christmas events around the region. (Pousner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 50.
</P>
<P>
   KANTNER _ Three questions with Paul Kantner, founder of the
Jefferson Airplane/Starship. (MLongino, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   PSYCHOLOGY-LECRONE _ Dr. Hap LeCrone's weekly psychology column.
(LeCrone, Waco Tribune-Herald) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD
</P>
<P>
   PUMPKINS _ There's more to pumpkin than jack-o'-lanterns, and
more to eat than pumpkin pie. Just ask Bonnie Mercuri of Bonnybrook
Farms in Centerville. She's been growing specialty pumpkins for
four years and this year her harvest of cooking pumpkins ranges
from an oversized muffin-shaped blue pumpkin called Queensland Blue
to tiny Wee B Little specimens that are true pumpkins, not gourds.
(Dayton Daily-News). 17. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   CANNED-PUMPKIN _ With apologies to Mom, I'll admit I keep a
couple of cans of pumpkin puree on the shelf. Recipes using canned
pumpkin and green pumpkin seeds. (Dayton Daily News). 25.
</P>
<P>
   PUMPKIN-STEW _ Recipe for Pumpkin Stew. (Dayton Daily News). 7.
</P>
<P>
   PUMPKIN-BOX _ A 6-pound pumpkin sitting on the kitchen counter
can be an intimidating ingredient. So when the recipe calls for
``peeled, seeded pumpkin cubes'' here's what you do. (Dayton Daily
News). 7.
</P>
<P>
   CRUMBS-COLUMN _ Kitty Crider's food column. (Crider, Austin
American-Statesman). WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   FOOD-DIETITIAN _ Ask a dietitian column. (Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   CORN-PUDDING _ Recipe for corn pudding. (Austin
American-Statesman).
</P>
