Vermont antiquing &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Foliage and antiquing make for a great outing. Just published is
Lisa Mullenneaux's ``Vermont Antiquing: Six Day Trips'' (Penington
Press, $9.95, 118 pp.). The book includes maps, listings of
dealers, ideas for dining and lodging, essays on what is an
antique, and tales of antiques pickers. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
