   qequassett.com. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Top hotel &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   You don't have to travel far to enjoy one of the world's best
hotels. The Four Seasons Hotel Boston continues to win accolades.
The hotel has just tied for 35th place in Travel and Leisure's
``World's Best'' ranking of the Top 100 Hotels in the Continental
US and Canada. The hotel is also the only Mobil Five-Star and AAA
Five-Diamond hotel in New England. ``We are constantly striving for
perfection, and recognition of this sort is the best reminder that
our efforts do not go unnoticed,'' said Robin Brown, Four Seasons
general manager. In the magazine's Best of Boston story, the
hotel's Aujourd'hui was highly rated for its cuisine, views of the
Public Garden, and ``near-perfect'' staff.
</P>
