Barnaby J. Feder.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-CORPORATE-PR (Tokyo) _ Corporate Japan has suddenly
awakened to the need for crisis control. Alarmed by how companies
like Mitsubishi Motors, Bridgestone and Snow Brand fumbled in
public relations blunders in recent months, other companies are
calling in PR consultants, scheduling training sessions and
rethinking how they handle a public crisis. By Miki Tanikawa.
</P>
<P>
   WORLD-BIZ-BRIEFS (Undated) _ Short items on business news from
around the world.
</P>
