   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ In a tactical victory for Microsoft
Corp., the Supreme Court declined Tuesday to immediately hear an
appeal of the government antitrust case against the software giant.
The case was sent instead to the U.S. Circuit Court of Appeals in
Washington, which is seen as more sympathetic to Microsoft than was
U.S. District Judge Thomas Penfield Jackson. (Hight).
