<P>
   DIABETES _ An international research team led by scientists at
the University of Chicago and the UT Health Science Center in
Houston has discovered a gene that makes certain people susceptible
to a form of diabetes common in Mexican Americans. The discovery,
published today in Nature Genetics, opens up a new pathway for
scientists to explore in preventing and treating this form of
diabetes called type-2, or adult-onset, diabetes. (Roser, Austin
American-Statesman)
