SAN FRANCISCO _  POP FOOD  _ At the start of the 21st century, when
more people than ever eat out, the restaurant has become a
pop-culture icon. Not only are chefs the new rock stars, but tales
from behind the swinging kitchen doors are obsessing people who a
decade ago couldn't have cared less about their waiter's opinion on
child-rearing or how a chef kicked a drug habit. &HT;    With 2 sidebars. 
 By Kim Severson  
 c. 2000 The San Francisco Chronicle  
