 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; SECRET-GOAT &LR;  _ Back when California cuisine was
just emerging, goat cheese became the lightening rod of ridicule
and wisecracks. Today goat cheese has gone mainstream and is about
as common as Gouda; but no dish is as uncommonly good as the
Twice-Baked Goat Cheese Souffle at Zax.
<P>
   With chef's secrets for success, recipe.
