   NASHVILLE-SYMPHONY (New York) _ On the Nashville Symphony at
Carnegie Hall. By Allan Kozinn.
</P>
<P>
   IRAN-BOOK-REVIEW (Undated) _ For many Americans, Iran conjures
up the hostage crisis, terrorism, the crowds chanting ``death to
America'' and the fierce Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini denouncing the
United States and Israel. Elaine Sciolino, a New York Times
correspondent, shows a different Iran in ``Persian Mirrors.''
Reviewed by Ira Lapidus.
</P>
