<P>
   NEW-ENGLAND-FOODS (Westport, Mass.) _ The southern coast of New
England is the source for oysters so fine they are sold by name,
and for wines that are served in some of the leading restaurants in
Boston and New York. One of the best American blue cheeses is made
here, not far from centuries-old apple orchards and farms that are
experimenting with cutting-edge technology in fish farming. In
Westport, they have a plan to preserve their rural coastline and to
make the region as famous for its food and wine as Sonoma County in
California or the Hudson Valley in New York state. By Marian
Burros. (With map)
</P>
<P>
   KOSHER-RESTAURANTS (Undated) _ For truly observant Jews, kosher
restaurants were traditionally the only alternative to staying home
or going to grandma's. Now those old-fashioned places have given
way to more modern kosher options _ Chinese, Japanese, Indian,
Mexican and French steakhouses among them. And the newest additions
to the kosher scene are high-end restaurants featuring ambitious
dishes like bison, rack of lamb and whole roasted sea bass, with
wine lists and elegant surroundings. By Alex Witchel. (With photos)
</P>
