<P>
   UNDATED _ The Texas drought is not over because it rained in a
few places, but talk of the drought might subside. That would be
welcome news to Elmer Kelton, the San Angelo writer who penned the
fictional, but defining, book on dry Texas weather, ``The Time It
Never Rained.'' ``Oh, it's still been dry out here,'' he said from
his home near the campus of Angelo State University. ``We haven't
had any rain since June, so people I run into invariably ask if I'm
going to do an update, or additional chapter, or another book.'' By
ART CHAPMAN. Story has moved in ``a'' general news category. &QL; 
