   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   LIBERIANS-DEADLINE (Undated) _ More than 10,000 Liberians who
fled their war-torn homeland in 1989 and have been living in refuge
the United States could lose their jobs on Friday, when their work
permits expire. By Cindy Rodriguez. 900 words. (a and i coding)
</P>
<P>
   HARVARD-SUIT (Undated)_ The U.S. Justice Department sues Harvard
University and others for up to $120 million for allegedly
mismanaging and defrauding a government-funded project in the
mid-1990s to help overhaul the Russian economy. By Patrick Healy.
1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   CELTIC-STABBING (Boston) __ Friends of Celtic Paul Pierce say
there was no earlier incident at another bar the night before he
was stabbed seven times and that Pierce was not targeted for
revenge. By Francie Latour and Shira Springer. 800 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT-APPEAL (Undated) _ Supreme Court sends the Microsoft
antitrust case to a federal appeals court, handing the computer
giant a victory by delaying the government's effort to break it in
two. By Hiawatha Bray. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   NEW-WINDOWS (Undated) _ Microsoft is king of the desktop, but
not well loved in America's corporations, where Windows isn't
considered stable enough to run business networks. Company to
announce a new platform to change that. By Alex Pham. 700 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HKN-BRUINS (Boston) _ Bruins re-sign center Joe Thornton and
