<SLUG> BC-CAMPAIGN-DEBATE-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GORE OUT OF LUCK FINDING PRE-DEBATE LODGING 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By ANNE KORNBLUT  
 c.2000 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ Al Gore wanted to spend the weekend at Cape Cod,
really he did.
</P>
<P>
   Unfortunately for the vice president, so do a lot of other
people. And they made their reservations first.
</P>
<P>
   Gore was planning to arrive on the Cape Friday night, spending
the next four days preparing for his debate against Republican
nominee George W. Bush.
</P>
<P>
   But when the Democrat's staff started making the arrangements,
it turned out there wasn't enough hotel space to accommodate the
200-250 reporters and staff who travel with the Gore campaign.
</P>
<P>
   ``Um, well, I guess the weather's been pretty good'' on the
Cape, and a lot of folks decided it would be a nice place to spend
a fall weekend, said Gore spokesman Doug Hattaway. The campaign
scoured both Boston and the Cape, and couldn't cobble together
enough rooms, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Gore will definitely spend Tuesday night _ the night of the
debate _ in town. But as for the weekend debate preparation locale,
``we're back to the drawing board,'' Hattaway said.
</P>
<P>
   The debate will include only Gore and Bush, as the bipartisan
commission organizing the event decided Tuesday to exclude all
minor candidates. The ruling means Green Party candidate Ralph
Nader and Reform Party candidate Pat Buchanan will not be allowed
to participate.
</P>
<P>
   The Commission on Presidential Debates had said previously that
the debates would be open only to candidates whose names were on
the ballot in enough states to theoretically win the election, and
who were getting at least 15 percent of voter support in national
opinion polls.
</P>
<P>
   ``Of this group, solely George Bush and Al Gore were found to
have achieved the criteria's requisite level of support in the
selected national public opinion polls,'' the commission said in a
statement.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
