   Photo clients will automatically receive our photos via AP's
PhotoExpress or may download them from either the Wieck Photo
Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at
213-237-4577 or PressLink at 800-888-6195. Non-clients can make
individual purchases by calling (888) 603-1036 or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT26) NEW YORK -- Sept. 26, 2000 -- FASHION-NYWOMEN5-HNS --
Designer Donna Karan chose soft colors and sheer fabrics for her
2001 women's spring collection. Her lineup includes deep-toned
petals or handkerchiefs of sheer gauze or chiffon. Topped with a
structured jacket or coat, the fluttering skirts give an ambivalent
message of strength and femininity for which Karan has long been
known. Karan's collection will also highlight collages of striped
chiffon, buff and pastel scarf dresses and sunset orange blouson
dresses and slips with diamante trim. (Buster Dean/The Houston
Chronicle)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT25) NEW YORK -- Sept. 26, 2000 -- FASHION-NYWOMEN4-HNS --
The fashion crowd bent on seeing designer John Bartlett's
collection entered a black and dimly lit tent to a pulsing sound
resembling the ping of submarine sonar. The audience was presented
with a wall of men, 50 buff bodies stacked on five levels, all the
men in white briefs and painted white from head to toe. Except one,
who was brilliant red. Some of Bartlett's collections are filled
with ideas and modern twists on couture techniques. (Buster
Dean/The Houston Chronicle) LITE
</P>
