<P>
   (NYT22) CENTERVILLE, Ohio -- Sept. 26, 2000 -- PUMPKINS-COX -
There's more to pumpkin than jack-o'-lanterns, and more to eat than
pumpkin pie. Just ask Bonnie Mercuri of Bonnybrook Farms in
Centerville. She's been growing specialty pumpkins for four years
and this year her harvest of cooking pumpkins ranges from an
oversized muffin-shaped blue pumpkin called Queensland Blue to tiny
Wee B Little specimens that are true pumpkins, not gourds. Cooking
pumpkins clockwise from the top: Jarrahdale, Whangaparoa, Winter
Luxury Pie, Rouge 'Vif d'Etampes, Long Island Cheese (center),
Queensland Blue, Buckskin. (Jim Witmer/Dayton Daily-News)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT21) NEW YORK -- Sept. 26, 2000 -- MRSCLINTON-DETRACTORS --
Being first lady isn't a job, Hillary Rodham Clinton said early
this year in Manhattan, ``it's a role.'' While making her one of
the most famous women in the world, her performance in that role
has driven nearly a decade of dinner-table speculation about the
scale of her ambition and the state of her marriage. Clinton is
greeted by supporters during a visit to the Riverdale Young Men's
and Young Women's Hebrew Association, Tuesday. (Librado Romero/The
New York Times)
</P>
<P>
