early Wednesday in Sydney. Mientkiewicz, the first baseman who was
banished to the Minnesota Twins' farm system this season, ended the
wettest and wackiest game in Olympic baseball history with a solo
homer in the ninth inning to beat South Korea 3-2 in the
semifinals. (Joey Ivansco/Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   (OLY17) UNDATED -- Sept. 26, 2000 -- OLY-BASEBALL-1 -- Doug
Mientkiewicz celebrates his game-winning home run, early Wednesday
in Sydney. Mientkiewicz, the first baseman who was banished to the
Minnesota Twins' farm system this season, ended the wettest and
wackiest game in Olympic baseball history with a solo homer in the
