Pierce at the New England Medical Center, Monday. Pierce was doing
well after doctors sewed up knife wounds in his face, neck, and
back including one that penetrated his abdomen and diaphragm and
hit his lung. Medical sources say he should recover enough to soon
play basketball for the Celtics. (Dominic Chavez/The Boston Globe)
