   (NYT6) ANN ARBOR, Mich. -- Sept. 26, 2000 -- GORE-CAMPAIGN --
Vice President Al Gore, the Democratic presidential candidate,
during the taping of MTV's ``Choose or Lose'' show at the
University of Michigan sponsored by MTV and Time magazine, Tuesday.
With a new poll out this week indicating that less than half of the
under-25 crowd will definitely vote in the November contest between
Gore and Republican George W. Bush, Gore tried to personalize the
election for MTV's young viewers as he appealed to them to ``fight
through'' any disillusionment. (Ruth Fremson/The New York Times)
