<HEADLINE>
PAUS NAMED STARTER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BILLY WITZ  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR;  LOS ANGELES _ Cory Paus, after throwing the ball crisply and
accurately in practice Tuesday, was officially named the starting
quarterback for Saturday night's game at the Rose Bowl against
Arizona State by UCLA coach Bob Toledo.
</P>
<P>
   ``Cory's doing a nice job,'' Toledo said. ``He appears to be
throwing the ball pretty well. It's not a panic deal. I'm doing it
because he's our starting quarterback, he's healthy and ready to
play.''
</P>
<P>
   Paus, who beat out Ryan McCann in fall camp, suffered a
separated right throwing shoulder on the first play of the season
opener against Alabama. McCann quarterbacked the Bruins to wins
over Alabama, Fresno State and Michigan before they were beaten by
Oregon.
</P>
<P>
   Paus, who was cleared to begin practicing on Monday, said he is
close to where he was before the injury. For the most part, he
looked it Tuesday, displaying more pace and accuracy than McCann.
</P>
<P>
   ``At certain times, I don't have as much zip on the ball,'' Paus
said. ``There were a few throws today where I ran into a couple of
people and I felt fine. That was a major thing.
</P>
<P>
   ``I was a little less rusty today than yesterday and I'll be a
little less rusty tomorrow than I was today. You have to play full
speed and wing it, as coach (Al) Borges would say.''
</P>
</TEXT>
