<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-VIOLENCE-KIDS-TEXT-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EXCERPTS FROM MARKET RESEARCH DOCUMENTS ON A VIOLENT FILM 
</HEADLINE>
   (With VIOLENCE-KIDS-FILMS)  
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Following are excerpts from documents of the National Research
Group, the dominant market research organization for major studios
about its work on the movie, ``I Know What You Did Last Summer.''
</P>
<P>
   Per our conversation here is a suggested research plan for ``I
Know What You Did Last Summer.''
</P>
<P>
   The survey will be conducted among those who saw the original
movie. Since the bulk of the audiences were moviegoers between 12
and 24, it is suggested that the sample be comprised mostly of 12-
to 24-year-olds, half between 12 and 17 and half between 18 and 24.
Although the original movie was R rated and the sequel will also be
R rated, there is evidence to suggest that attendance at the
original dipped down to the age of 10. Therefore, it seems to make
sense to interview 10- to 11-year-olds as well. In addition we will
survey African-American and Latino moviegoers between the ages of
10 and 24.
</P>
<P>
   The lines of questioning will include, but not be limited to the
following:
</P>
<P>
   ABOUT THE FIRST MOVIE:
</P>
<P>
   favorite character &QL;
</P>
<P>
   other liked characters &QL;
</P>
<P>
   most memorable scene &QL;
</P>
<P>
   favorite scene &QL;
</P>
<P>
   other scenes liked &QL;
</P>
<P>
   scariest scene &QL;
</P>
<P>
   THE SAMPLE &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The sample will be comprised of 500 moviegoers between the ages
of 12 and 24 and 100 moviegoers between the ages of 9 and 11. In
addition 150 African-Americans and Latinos between the ages of 12
and 24 and 50 between the ages of 9 and 11 equally divided by
gender will be interviewed. Therefore, in total 900 interviews will
be carried out.
</P>
<P>
   THE ANALYSIS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   This research will determine who are the most intense fans of
the movie by age, gender, ethnicity, etc. and what drives their
zeal. The results will also define the primary and secondary
targets and what about the movie most appeals to them. It will also
provide information on the key aspects of the original movie most
liked and guidance for the direction of the second movie.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
